article.description: Margo Dydek scored 16 points and had 11 rebounds for her seventh double-double of the season to lead the Utah Starzz over the Indiana Fever 82-69 on Wednesday.
article.headline: Dydek powers Utah with seventh double-double
article.linkText: Scott-Richardson's 31 not enough as Starzz top Fever
article.story:
INDIANAPOLIS (AP) -- Utah's Margo Dydek and Indiana's Olympic Scott-Richardson were familiar foes Wednesday, and both centers put on quite a show. The 7-foot-2 Dydek scored 16 points, had 11 rebounds and four blocked shots to lead the Starzz over the Fever 82-69. Utah (12-6) overcame a career-high 31 point performance by Scott-Richardson, a teammate of Dydek when they began their WNBA careers in 1998 with the Starzz. ''I know her style of play. I used to practice against her every day,'' Scott-Richardson said. ''Just knowing she is not very aggressive and if I attacked her, she would be on her heels.'' Scott-Richardson, who had 19 in sparking a second-half comeback bid by Indiana, but all five starters finished in double figures for Utah, which didn't get a point from its reserves. Adrienne Goodson led Utah with 21 points, while Jennifer Azzi, Natalie Williams and Marie Ferdinand each had 15 apiece. Indiana rookie Tamika Catchings, selected a starter in the upcoming All-Star game, struggled to get an open shot. She missed her first eight shots and finished with 15. Reserve Bridget Pettis also had 15 for Indiana (8-10). ''She was attacking Margo,'' said Utah coach Candi Harvey, who was an assistant coach when Scott-Richardson was with the team. ''If it had been up to me, I wouldn't have traded her. But, if I need to pick my poison I'd let her have 31 and their team only with 60 just as long as we win. ''You can't double team Catchings and Nikki (McCray). That's why Olympia scored 31.'' Utah shot a season-high 60.4 percent from the field _ the second-highest in franchise history. The Starzz hit 16 of 24 shots in the second half. ''Our offense just flowed,'' Harvey said. Goodson, meanwhile, credited a defense that limited Indiana to shooting 31.5 from the field. ''We played great defense,'' Goodson said. ''We know that to get to the next level we have to defend people consistently.'' The Starzz pulled away in the final eight minutes after Indiana cut a 34-23 halftime deficit to six. Azzi hit a jumper to start the run and make it 60-52. The Fever trailing by only 11 at halftime despite shooting just 19 percent from the field. Intimidated by Dydek inside, the Fever consistently looked for the 3-point shot but it wasn't there. Indiana was only 1-of-10 from 3-point range in the first half and shot just 7-of-37 overall. Dydek and Williams had three blocks apiece in the half. ''In the first half, it affected our driving the middle,'' Pettis said of Dydek. ''We adjusted in the second half. We just didn't hit shots we normally hit.'' The game was close until the final minutes of the first half. Two free throws by Catchings cut Utah's lead to 20-19 with 4:51 remaining in the period. Utah then pulled away with a 14-2 run to take a 34-21 advantage. Williams had six in the run. Game notes
Scott-Richardson's previous high was 19 against Charlotte on June 29, 2001, and her high this season had been 15 twice. ... Dydek's seven double-doubles rank her third in the WNBA, behind Chamique Holdsclaw's nine and Lisa Leslie's eight. ... Indiana set franchise records of just five turnovers and 73 attempts from the field.
